The paper deals with offline signature verification using a convolutional Siamese network, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with document forensics, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of machine learning techniques for feature extraction and classification makes it relevant to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques for minimizing and maximizing distances, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is relevant to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
